    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="765"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.00/498.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Bundy</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British <hi rend="italic">Highflyer</hi> arrived Monrovia yesterday. Informed
                    that Commander states to President he was ordered here by British Government to
                    offer Liberian Government assistance in Kru disturbances until arrival <hi
                        rend="italic">Chester</hi>. Liberian Government, having appealed to the
                    Government of the United States for aid, prefers not to avail itself of British
                    assistance except so advised by the Government of the United States.
                    Disturbances unabated but measures already <pb facs="0746" n="630"
                        xml:id="pg_630"/> taken deemed sufficient to hold situation until <hi
                        rend="italic">Chester</hi> arrives November 1. Liberian Government awaits
                    Department’s advice before answering Commander.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bundy.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
